QUANTUM HARMONIC OSCILLATOR — RDG FORM

SID (Structure):
    ξ = sqrt(mω/ħ) x
    H_n(ξ)  Hermite polynomials
    ψ_n(x) = N H_n(ξ) exp(-ξ²/2)

PED (Dynamics):
    a  = sqrt(mω/(2ħ)) ( x + (i/(mω)) p )
    a† = sqrt(mω/(2ħ)) ( x - (i/(mω)) p )
    N = a† a
    H = ħω (N + 1/2)

Q-slice (Closure):
    exp(-ξ²/2) moderates the Hermite tower
    ensures ∫ |ψ_n|² dx = 1
    enforces finite-energy closure

Energy:
